post_cb({"33846613": {"ParentId": "33846577", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "2", "Body": "<p>In C you can. In C++ you can't.</p>\n<p>Quoting the C++ standard (\u00a73.6.1.3):</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_33846577_33846613_0\">The function <code>main</code> shall not be used within a program.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>There's nothing in the C standard forbidding calling <code>main</code>.</p>\n<p>Whether or not calling <code>main</code> is good design is quite opinion-based, but usually one would be better off using a loop instead.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "3425536", "LastEditorUserId": "3425536", "LastEditDate": "2015-11-21T18:04:45.343", "Id": "33846613", "Score": "10", "CreationDate": "2015-11-21T17:49:20.510", "LastActivityDate": "2015-11-21T18:04:45.343"}, "33846612": {"ParentId": "33846577", "CommentCount": "3", "Body": "<p>You've already determined it is possible. However, it makes your entire program recursive. It also could make your code a little harder to understand.</p>\n<p>So it's really hard for me to imagine any <em>pros</em> for this.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "522663", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "33846612", "Score": "1", "CreationDate": "2015-11-21T17:49:17.727", "LastActivityDate": "2015-11-21T17:49:17.727"}, "33846669": {"ParentId": "33846577", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>According to C++ standard</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_33846577_33846669_0\">5.2.2.9  \"Recursive calls are permitted, except to the function named main\"</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "OwnerUserId": "3777958", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "33846669", "Score": "6", "CreationDate": "2015-11-21T17:53:57.983", "LastActivityDate": "2015-11-21T17:53:57.983"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_33846577_33846669_0": {"section_id": 5996, "quality": 0.625, "length": 5}}, "n3337": {"so_33846577_33846669_0": {"section_id": 5764, "quality": 0.875, "length": 7}}, "n4659": {"so_33846577_33846669_0": {"section_id": 7497, "quality": 0.625, "length": 5}}}, "33846577": {"CommentCount": "4", "ViewCount": "154", "ClosedDate": "2015-11-21T18:01:08.580", "CreationDate": "2015-11-21T17:46:14.337", "LastActivityDate": "2015-11-21T18:04:45.343", "PostTypeId": "1", "FavoriteCount": "1", "Title": "Is the main function callable in C++ or C", "Id": "33846577", "Score": "2", "Body": "<p>Can I call the main method in C/C++ from other functions. it seems to work but I do not know if it is a good software design in c++. please tell me the pros and cons ? \nThank you.  </p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c><c++11>", "OwnerUserId": "3491012", "AnswerCount": "3"}});